[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(5) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Son of Nathan.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Probably Nathan, son of David, and own brother of Solomon (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 3:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), is here intended; for the title ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Cohen, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "here given to Zabud, is expressly ascribed in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Samuel 8:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to the “sons of David;” and Nathan the prophet always has his title, “the prophet,” appended to his name wherever first mentioned in this book. (See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Kings 1:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Kings 1:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Kings 1:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Kings 1:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Azariah is the “chief of the officers”—that is, chief over the twelve officers mentioned below (1Kings 4:7-19)—living, however, at Court.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Azariah ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "is the “chief of the officers”—that is, chief over the twelve officers mentioned below (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Kings 4:7-19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")—living, however, at Court.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Zabud, besides the title of Cohen, has that of “the king’s friend,” previously given to Hushai (2Samuel 15:37; 2Samuel 16:16), and apparently indicating special intimacy and wisdom as a “privy counsellor.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Zabud, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "besides the title of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Cohen, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "has that of “the king’s friend,” previously given to Hushai (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Samuel 15:37",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Samuel 16:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), and apparently indicating special intimacy and wisdom as a “privy counsellor.”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
