  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:5-6",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 4:5-6",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The son of Nathan was over the officers — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Over those twelve officers named ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c., who were all to give up their accounts to him. The Hebrew word, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "נצבים",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "nitsabim, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "here, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", rendered officers, signifies any governors, or commanders of the higher sort. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 8:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Zabud the son of Nathan — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The prophet, who had been so highly instrumental in establishing Solomon on the throne; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was principal officer — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Possibly president of the king’s council. The Hebrew word is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "כהן",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cohen, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and generally, is rendered ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "priest, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "although, as we have observed there, it may also be translated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "prince. And the king’s friend — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "His confidant, with whom he used to communicate his most secret counsels. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ahishar was over the household — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Steward of the king’s house. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Over the tribute — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The personal tribute, or levy of men, as appears by comparing this with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 5:13-14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; it being very fit that there should be some one person to whom the chief conduct or inspection of that great business should be committed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
